Name: capture
Description: Screen capture tools (screenshot).
Version: 1.0

Overview:
This tool allows capturing a screenshot of the current screen and saving it
as a PNG file.

Commands:
- capture_screen
- capture_region
- capture_all_screens
  Capture a screenshot of the screen.
  Parameters:
  - path (string, optional): Output file path. If omitted, a timestamped
    file is created in the current working directory.

Usage Examples:
- capture_screen
- capture_screen path="C:\\Users\\bismi\\Pictures\\screen1.png"

Behavior Notes:
- Creates parent directories if they do not exist.
- Output format is PNG.

Dependencies:
- Pillow (PIL) for ImageGrab
